c instance value and a transient metaobject. I also need to ensure that I initialize `CLASS_METAOBJECT` correctly, and then proceed with setting the metaobject and asserting the field accesses properly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java object serialization**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out an issue with a Java object, particularly with the deserialization process. There's a metaobject field that's transient and null, which complicates things since the method read doesn't seem to set the metaobject. I'm also wondering if I need to check the serialVersionUID for any potential warnings. Then I’ll need to inspect other tests to see if they adhere to the same rules regarding serial UID.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_KnSCocBgHCWCalURxX5hsPyQ|fc_0ab201cfd4f1d1740169fee56eb7c081a3b3054961e297ba9e", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jboss.weld/weld-osgi-bundle/1.1.0.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_weld/weld_osgi_bundle/JavassistLoaderTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 940, "output": 642, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20014, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778312545868, "responseId": "resp_0ab201cfd4f1d1740169fee56266c481a3b50bf1de66f96564"}}
